Items.Content:
Preprocessor Directives

//				Comment to end of line
/* */				Multiline Comment
#include<*.*>			Include standard header file
#include"*.*"			Include file in current directory
#define X some text		Replace X with some text
#define X \
	some text		Line continuation
#undef X				Remove definition
#if defined(X) [#ifdef X]		Conditional compilation
#if !defined(X) [#ifndef X]		Conditional compilation
#else				Optional (use after #ifdef X)
#endif				Required after #ifdef X\#ifndef X

Literals

255, 0377, 0xff			Integers (decimal, octal, hex)
2147483647L, 0x7fffffffl		Long (32-Bit) integers
123.0, 1.23e2			Double precision numbers
'a', '\141', '\x61'			Character (literal, octal, hex)
'\n', '\\', '\'', '\"'			Newline, backslash, single\double quote
"string\n"				Array of characters ending in newline
"hello" "world"			Concatenated strings
true, false			Boolean constants 1 and 0

Declarations

int x;				Declare x to be of integer type
int x=255;			Declare and initialize x to 255
short s; long l;			16 or 32-Bit integer
char c = 'a';			8-Bit character
unsigned char u=255;		char is either signed or unsigned
signed char s=-1;			char is either signed or unsigned
unsigned long x=0xffffffffL;		short\int\long have signs
float f; double d;			Single or double precision decimal
bool b=true;			true or false, 1 or 0
int a, b, c;			Multiple declarations
int a[10];				Array of 10 ints
int a[]={0,1,2};			Initialized array
int a[2][2]={{1,2},{3,4}}		Multidimensional array
char s[]="hello";			String
int* p;				p is a pointer to a memory address
char* s="hello"			s points to char array "hello"
void* p=NULL;			Address of untyped memory
int& r=x;				r is a reference to int x
enum weekend {SAT,SUN};		weekend can only be SAT or SUN
enum weekend day;		day is of weekend type
enum weekend {SAT=0, SUN=1};	Representation as int
enum {SAT,SUN} day;		Anonymous enum
typedef String char*;		String s; = char* s;
const int c=3;			Constants cannot be assigned to
const int* p=a;			Contents of p are constant
int* const p=a;			p is constant, not contents
const int* const p=a;		p and contents are constant
const int& cr=x;			cr cannot change value of x

Storage Classes

int x;				Memory exists only while in scope
static int x;			Global lifetime
extern int x;			Information only, defined elsewhere

Statements

x=y;				Expressions are statements
int x;				Declarations are statements
;				Empty statement
{				Blocks are one statement
int x;				x's scope lasts until end of block
}				End of block
if (x) a;				If x is true (non 0), evaluate a
else if (y) b;			If not x and y
else c;				If not x or y
while (x) a;			Repeat while x is true
for (x;y;z) a;			x; while(y) {a; z;}
do a; while (x);			a; while(x) a;
switch(x){				x must be int
case X1: a;			If x==X1, evaluate a
case X2: b;			Else if x==X2, evaluate b
default: c;			Else jump here
}				End of switch
break;				End while, do, for, switch loop
continue;				Goto bottom of while, do, for loop
return x;				Return x to caller
try{a;}				Attempt to evaluate statement(s)
catch(T t) {b;}			If a throws type T, evaluate b
catch (...) {c;}			If a throws other type, evaluate c
